Name: Bieda
Text: I can't take it anymore! I suffer from insomnia and my hair is falling out.

Name: Therapist
Text: Don't you think, It's because you're getting older?

Name: Bieda
Text: No! It all has started since I took money from that local guy 1100 years ago.

Name: Bieda
Text: He has started coming to my place with shovels and digged it all out to find his pouch.

Name: Therapist
Text: And how did you feel about it?

Name: Bieda
Text: Well, I didn't like it. But, I thought at first: 'I might feed myself with his fear'.

Name: Therapist
Text: Don't you think that's a bit cruel?

Name: Bieda
Text: It is my job to make them fear, poor and bring misfortune.

Name: Therapist
Text: Sure, just remember to pay me after our session...

Name: Therapist
Text: Tell me about your first time meeting him...
